   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FIVE THE REQUIREMENTS FOR THE MINISTRY OF THE NEW TESTAMENT PRIESTS OF THE GOSPEL Scripture Reading: Prov 4:18; 2 Cor 4:16; Gal 5:25; Rom 8:4; Phil 2:14; Gal 5:26; 1 Cor 1:10; Eph 4:14; 1 Tim 1:3-4; Matt 26:41; Rom 12:11; Col 1:29; 1 Cor 15:58; Phil 3:20; 2 Cor 5:10 OUTLINE Being revived every morning Prov 4:18.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Overcoming every day 2 Cor 4:16.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Living in the Spirit every moment Gal 5:25.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Walking according to the spirit in everything Rom 8:4: Without murmurings and reasonings Phil 2:14.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Without selfish intentions and greedy ambitions Gal 5:26.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Being in one accord and in harmony with the saints 1 Cor 1:10.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Not being blown by the winds of teaching Eph 4:14.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Not teaching anything different from the truth concerning the New Testament priesthood of the gospel of God 1 Tim 1:3-4.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Watching prayerfully, laboring diligently, and struggling earnestly to carry out each step of the duties of the New Testament priests of the gospel of God Matt 26:41; Rom 12:11; Col 1:29; 1 Cor 15:58.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Awaiting the Lord's coming by living and working in the light of His judgment seat Phil 3:20; 2 Cor 5:10.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>In the past few messages we have seen that the New Testament priests of the gospel of God should do the following four main things: first, go out to preach the gospel to save sinners; second, nourish and care for the new believers; third, teach and perfect the saints; and fourth, prophesy for the building up of the church.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>These matters, especially the last two, are very much involved with the aspect of practice.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>How should we ask and answer questions in the group meetings?</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>How should we learn?</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>How should we teach?</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Furthermore, prophesying in the meetings is a particularly new matter.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>How can we change our meetings from one person speaking and everyone else listening to all speaking and listening mutually?</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>We all want to learn these matters.</S>
   </TEXT>
